State Bank of New Boston, Appellant, v. Josie F. Bridger, Appellee.Gen. No. 5,771.

(Not to be reported in full.)

Appeal from the Circuit Court of Mercer county; the Hon. Prank D. Ramsay, Judge, presiding. Heard in this court at the April term, 1913.Affirmed.Opinion filed August 2, 1913.

Statement of the Case.

Action on a note by State Bank of New Boston against Josie F. Bridger. From a judgment for defendant, plaintiff appeals.

This case is controlled by the decision in State Banlc of New Boston v. Livingston, Gen. No. 5,770, ante, p. 529.W. J. Graham, for appellant.Church & Church, for appellee. Mr. Presiding Justice Whitney

delivered the opinion of the court.
